# Shared — Cron Outbox Relay Trigger
# TD24-S01: publishes the cron-outbox-relay trigger, dispatched to OutboxRelayTriggerHandler,
# which runs the outbox sweep (grace-window batch, SKIP LOCKED) + retention GC in one tick. In
# production, Cloud Scheduler publishes the same trigger directly to Pub/Sub (M17-S21) — this
# endpoint is the local/manual trigger path only, protected by the global InternalApiGuard
# (X-Internal-Key), not PubSubPushGuard.
# Response is { ok: true } once the trigger is published — it does not wait for the sweep to
# finish. Requires the Pub/Sub emulator running (pnpm infra:up); check backend logs for
# "trigger received by outbox-relay" to confirm dispatch.
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. pnpm infra:up
#   2. pnpm --filter @ikaro/backend run migration:run
#   3. pnpm --filter @ikaro/backend run dev

@baseUrl = {{backendUrl}}

### POST /cron/outbox-relay — publish the cron-outbox-relay trigger
POST {{baseUrl}}/cron/outbox-relay
X-Internal-Key: {{internalKey}}

###
